The entry recording an 655611 011 the eyre rolls usually specifies, as directed hythe Chapters of the Regard, the name of the lord to whose fee the assart belongs. By the lord of the see is meant the person of whom the tenant of the assart ought to hold.l Information on this point would always be useful in identifying the property. Moreover, as a lord must in general have been a consenting party to the assarting and sowing of his tenant, it was desirable that the justices should have his name in order that they might render him responsible if his tenant made default.
